    "Body": " Drug & Alcohol Counselor Fairhaven Healthcare Center - Lowell, MA Quick Apply Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $54,000 - $73,000 a year Qualifications Addiction Counseling Grant Writing LADC Licensed Psychologist Credentials LICSW Master's Degree Full Job Description Welcome to Fairhaven Healthcare Center! We thank you for taking your valuable time and considering your next career move to our beautiful 169 bed facility located across the street from Lowell General Hospital. If you think you have what it takes to be part of an elite team, then we hope that you will forward us your resume. We look forward to meeting you! SUMMARY: We are looking for a Champion and Leader for our one of a kind, innovative program focused on the adult and senior populations that are suffering from the disease of addiction. We call this our Circle of Hope suite of services and we are the first Skilled Nursing Facility in the State to present such a complete offering. Our Circle patients have completed their detox at another appropriate facility and are now admitted to Fairhaven based on other serious clinical needs such as COPD & CHF. While being treated for these comorbidities, it is our hope to introduce them to recovery techniques that may assist them further, when they return to the community. A small sampling includes AA Meetings, Smart Recovery Meetings, Yoga Relaxation, Meditation and one on one counseling with a licensed Psychologist. We are in search of a strong leader who can help us to further develop and continuously improve upon this unique offering. You will be responsible for the entire Circle population; developing strategy, direction and focus of the Circle of Hope. Designing, writing and implementing policies and procedures; training Fairhaven staff; providing one on one, and group counseling; ensuring regulations are adhered to; completing and verifying completion of necessary paperwork; be involved with Community and marketing activities; and more. You will report directly to the Executive Administrator. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS: A Master\u2019s degree in Health Education, Public Health, Clinical Social Work, or related content area strongly preferred; a Licensed Alcohol and Drug Counselor in Massachusetts preferred; Licensed Clinical Social Worker (LICSW) also preferred; a minimum of 1 - 3 years\u2019 experience in counseling in a substance abuse program; or any equivalent combination of education and experience. Experience with grant writing preferred. Job Type: Full-time Experience: drug and alcohol counseling in a clinical environment: 1 year (Required) License: Licensed Drug and Alcohol Counselor in the State of Massachu (Required) "
